
Overview of noun colon

The noun colon has 5 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                          
1. (2) colon -- (the part of the large intestine between the cecum and the rectum; it extracts moisture from food residues before they are excreted)
2. colon, El Salvadoran colon -- (the basic unit of money in El Salvador; equal to 100 centavos)
3. colon, Costa Rican colon -- (the basic unit of money in Costa Rica; equal to 100 centimos)
4. Colon, Aspinwall -- (a port city at the Caribbean entrance to the Panama Canal)
5. colon -- (a punctuation mark (:) used after a word introducing a series or an example or an explanation (or after the salutation of a business letter))
